# React & TypeScript Patterns

## Components
- Functional components only; named exports for features/pages
- Colocate feature-specific subcomponents under `src/features/<name>/`
- Layout shells: `AuthLayout`, `ConsoleLayout`, `LoginShell`, `AuthShell` in `src/components/layout/`
- Brand/avatars: `GateForgeBrand`, `DefaultAvatar` — reuse in pages, don't duplicate markup

## Route mounting (match existing pattern)
- **Auth screens** (Pattern A): wire feature forms in `routes/index.tsx` inside `AuthLayout` — no page file
- **Settings/console** (Pattern B): page in `src/pages/` composes features; console pages call admin query hooks directly

## Forms
- React Hook Form + `zodResolver` + schemas from `src/auth/schemas.ts` (or feature-local Zod schemas)
- Submit handlers: set local error state from `ApiError`; use loading flags for buttons

```tsx
// ✅ Pattern from login-form.tsx
try {
  await login(values, returnTo)
} catch (err) {
  setError(err instanceof ApiError ? err.message : 'Sign in failed')
}
```

## Auth
- Consume auth via `useAuth()` hook — don't duplicate token logic in features
- Protected/guest/admin routing via `ProtectedRoute`, `GuestRoute`, `AdminRoute`

## Server state (admin console)
- Define hooks in `features/admin/use-admin-queries.ts`; call them from console **pages**
- Stable query keys via `adminQueryKeys`; mutations invalidate via `useQueryClient`
- Shared loading/error/empty UI: `features/admin/console-state.tsx` (`ConsoleLoadingState`, etc.)
- Display formatting: `features/admin/admin-utils.ts`

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes; design tokens in `src/index.css` (`surface`, `on-surface`, etc.)
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- shadcn-style components in `src/components/ui/` — extend, don't fork unnecessarily

## API types
- Response shape: `ApiEnvelope<T>` with `data` + `meta`
- Discriminated unions for login (`LoginResult` vs MFA challenge) — use type guards like `isMfaChallenge`

## Env vars
- Read via `import.meta.env.VITE_*` — document in `.env.example`
- Feature flags: `VITE_GOOGLE_FEDERATION_ENABLED`, `VITE_DEFAULT_TENANT_ID`
